plot: Bodie's disastrous sales efforts result in a tongue lashing from Stringer Bell. Ziggy pulls Johnny Fifty into a new caper that makes the Greeks pay big money. McNulty goes undercover in a brothel. As Valchek fumes over the change of targets and Burrell pulls the rug from beneath him, Daniels and Pearlman maintain their composure.—Anonymous

Bodie's new corner erupts in violence when the former occupants try to take it back. Rawls responds with a series of large-scale arrests throughout the Western district, working in tandem with disillusioned district commander, Maj. Howard 'Bunny' Colvin (Robert Wisdom). As McNulty goes undercover as a john, the detail is confused at the lack of activity from the checkers, and realise they must have changed their operating procedure, with their wire on the warehouse now relatively useless. Meanwhile, Ziggy hatches a plan to make some money independently of Nick, and Stringer meets with Prop Joe to discuss turning over Westside territory in exchange for a cut of the profits from Joe's superior product.—Bertaut
